                <head>127. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On April 2, 1964, President Johnson met with the National Security Council at its
                    525th meeting at noon to discuss U.S. policy towards a number of countries and
                    issues. The meeting began with a briefing by Director of Central Intelligence
                        <persName corresp="#p_MCJA1">McCone</persName>. President Johnson then asked
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> if he had any matters he
                    wanted to add. According to a summary record, prepared by <persName
                        corresp="#p_SB1">Bromley Smith</persName> on April 2, <persName
                        corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> made the following points on Cambodia:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<hi rend="italic">Cambodia</hi>—<persName corresp="#p_SPN1"
                                >Sihanouk</persName> has made a turn-around, and, therefore, the
                            critical situation in Cambodia is improved. Developments will slow down
                            because <persName corresp="#p_SPN1">Sihanouk</persName> is taking a
                            vacation and visiting France. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BCE1"
                                >Bohlen</persName> is seeing De Gaulle today in an effort to
                            persuade the General to issue a statement clarifying French policy in
                            Southeast Asia. The hope is that De Gaulle would issue a statement that
                            his support of neutralization applies in the future and the immediate
                            present.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Cambodia was not discussed further at the meeting according to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SB1">Smith</persName>ʼs account. (Johnson Library, National
                    Security File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>, Meetings Files)</p>
            </div>
